trials.freeResponse: The tomas click when tested. They have a funnel like shape and have a light reddish color.
Griffs have about a 50% chance to whistle when tested. They have an octagonal shape and are blue.
Blickets squeak when tested. They are yellow and have a diamond like shape.
Daxes have about a 50% chance to beep when tested. They are red and have a circular shape like a can.
Wugs probably have a 1% chance to boom or lower when tested. They have a light blue cubical shape.
Feps probably have a 1% chance or lower to ring when tested. They are triangular and are red.

trials.response: The task consists of exploring different 3D shapes that had a set chance to make a particular noise.
